  "cooking_instructions": [
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Before you start cooking, take your <strong>chicken</strong> out of the fridge, open the packet and let it air</p><p>Boil a full kettle</p><p>Trim, then cut your <strong>green beans</strong> in half</p><p>Bash your <strong>lemongrass</strong> with a <strong>rolling pin</strong>, cut down the middle lengthways, remove the <strong>tough outer layers</strong> and set aside for later, then roughly chop the<strong> softer inner core[s]</strong></p>",
      "order": 1,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-1-1704810309770-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-1-1704810309770-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-1-1704810309770-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-1-1704810309770-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-1-1704810309770-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Add your <strong>basmati rice</strong> and 300ml <span class=\"text-purple\">[390ml]</span> <span class=\"text-danger\">[600ml]</span> <strong>cold</strong> <strong>water</strong> and the <strong>tough</strong> <strong>outer lemongrass layers </strong>to a pot with a lid and bring to the boil over a high heat</p><p>Once boiling, reduce the heat to low and add the <strong>chopped green beans</strong></p><p>Cook, covered, for 10-12 min or until all the water has absorbed and the rice and green beans are cooked</p><p>Once done, remove from the heat and keep covered until serving – this is your <strong>green bean rice</strong></p>",
      "order": 2,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-2-1704810310573-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-2-1704810310573-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-2-1704810310573-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-2-1704810310573-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-2-1704810310573-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>While the rice and beans are cooking, peel and quarter your<strong> shallot</strong></p><p>Crush your <strong>garlic</strong> open by squashing it with the side of a knife and discard the skins</p><p>Crush your <strong>cardamom pods</strong> open by squashing them with the side of a knife and discard the outer green skins</p>",
      "order": 3,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-3-1704810313542-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-3-1704810313542-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-3-1704810313542-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-3-1704810313542-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-3-1704810313542-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Add your <strong>cardamom seeds</strong>, <strong>soft innner core </strong>of the <strong>lemongrass</strong> and <strong>chopped shallot </strong>to a <strong>food processor </strong>with your <strong>crushed garlic</strong> and <strong>ginger paste</strong></p><p>Add <strong>half</strong> your <strong>chilli flakes </strong>(can't handle the heat? Go easy!) with your <strong>ground cinnamon </strong>(not a fan of cinnamon? Only add a little!)<strong> </strong>and 1 tsp <span class=\"text-purple\">[1 ½ tsp]</span><strong> </strong><span class=\"text-danger\">[2 tsp] </span><strong>sugar </strong>and blitz until smooth – this is your <strong>rendang paste</strong></p>",
      "order": 4,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-4-1704810316107-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-4-1704810316107-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-4-1704810316107-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-4-1704810316107-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-4-1704810316107-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Heat a large, wide-based pan (preferably non-stick) with a drizzle of<strong> vegetable</strong> <strong>oil</strong> over a medium-high heat</p><p>Once hot, add your <strong>free range chicken thighs</strong> with a pinch of <strong>salt </strong>and cook for 4-5 min on one side or until lightly browned  </p><p>Once browned, flip the thighs and add the <strong>rendang paste </strong>and your <strong>lime leaves </strong>and cook for a further 4-5 min or until the thighs are evenly browned and the paste is fragrant</p>",
      "order": 5,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-5-1704810317057-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-5-1704810317057-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-5-1704810317057-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-5-1704810317057-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-5-1704810317057-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>While the chicken is cooking, chop your <strong>creamed coconut</strong> roughly (if required!)</p><p>Dissolve the<strong> chopped creamed coconut</strong> in 250ml <span class=\"text-purple\">[325ml]</span><span class=\"text-danger\">[425ml]</span> <strong>boiled water</strong> with your <strong>chicken stock mix </strong>and <strong>fish sauce</strong>– this is your <strong>coconut stock</strong></p>",
      "order": 6,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-6-1704810321254-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-6-1704810321254-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-6-1704810321254-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
